   "source": [
    "# Using Queries\n",
    "\n",
    "Queries are a new user friendly way to use Textract by asking questions and getting answer. \n",
    "\n",
    "## Installation\n",
    "\n",
    "To begin, install the `amazon-textract-textractor` package using pip.\n",
    "\n",
    "`pip install amazon-textract-textractor`\n",
    "\n",
    "There are various sets of dependencies available to tailor your installation to your use case. The base package will have sensible default, but you may want to install the PDF extra dependencies if your workflow uses PDFs with `pip install amazon-textract-textractor[pdf]`. You can read more on extra dependencies [in the documentation](https://aws-samples.github.io/amazon-textract-textractor/installation.html)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Examples of queries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "8edf33e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.PngImagePlugin.PngImageFile image mode=RGBA size=1017x1273>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "Image.open(\"../../../tests/fixtures/form.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "00a6d5e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This form contains several fields and the Queries API allows us to \"ask\" 15 questions when using the synchronous API and 30 questions when using the asynchronous API.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the above we will ask the following questions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "bc07cda4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "queries = [\n",
    "    \"How many persons are there in the household?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the home phone number?\",\n",
    "    \"Are any household members non-citizen?\",\n",
    "    \"Are any household members disabled?\",\n",
    "    \"Where is the household located?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the email address?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the address of the landlord?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the telephone number of the landlord\",\n",
    "    \"What is the dwelling type?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the dwelling cost?\",\n",
    "    \"How did we hear about the Energy Assistance Program?\"\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0e7a29ce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Calling Textract"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "bbb4da26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from textractor import Textractor\n",
    "from textractor.data.constants import TextractFeatures\n",
    "\n",
    "extractor = Textractor(profile_name=\"default\")\n",
    "document = extractor.analyze_document(\n",
    "    file_source=Image.open(\"../../../tests/fixtures/form.png\"),\n",
    "    features=[TextractFeatures.QUERIES],\n",
    "    queries=queries\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "ca06e34d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

      ]

    }
   ],

    "document.queries"
   ]
  },

    "for query in document.queries:\n",
    "    if query.result:\n",
    "        print(f\"{query.query}\\n\\tAnswer: {query.result.answer}\\n\\tConfidence: {query.result.confidence}\\n\")\n",

  {

   "source": [
    "## Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Queries are a powerful and inexpensive solution for processing a smaller number of keys and values. However, you can run into issues where the result is wrong either because the question requires a higher-level understanding, as with \"How many people are there in the household?\". We recommend testing your workflow with some real samples and fine-tuning your queries to fit your use case."
   ]
  }
